# Regulatory Disclosures Offshoring Indicator

## identifier
de13107

## type
boolean

## definition
This indicates whether the service provided is classified as offshoring.  Offshoring means the outsourcing of a material business activity to a service provider where the outsourced activity is to be conducted outside Australia.

## guidance
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. 
true = The service provided is classified as offshoring. 
false = The service provided is not classified as offshoring.

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=RegulatoryDisclosures.Offshoring.Indicator
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.15
- period=instant
